      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FURY (4) deserves to win after a string of good runs. Tested at the mile for the first time last time and after settling off speed kept coming and just missed. Can go one better. THE ALBION (6) tried to lead throughout here at the mile two back and was claimed own the line. Wasn't for catching last time though, lifting to score a half-length win. Down in weight and has the inside so looks the one to catch again. VIERI (2) is fitter for two runs back and looks close to a win. THE ACCELATOR (7) is on a 10-day back-up after filling the minor placing behind FURY last time. Among the winning hopes. VILLA SEVENTYNINE (3) rates highly and is expected to do much better with that run under his belt.",
